Reckless Kelly (Austin, TX)

RECKLESS KELLY Long Night Moon -- September 2013 Austin's own Reckless Kelly return with their 8th studio album, "Long Night Moon" on September 3, 2013. The album is the follow-up to 2011's Grammy Nominated "Good Luck & True Love," which took home four Lone Star Music Awards, and sent three singles to #1 on Texas Radio. Reckless Kelly is an American country rock band. Formed in Idaho, the band moved to Austin, Texas in January 1997 and is now based there. The band's name was inspired by the Australian bushranger, Ned Kelly.
